quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  18,35,"Having thus harmed his own soul, he entered his garden saying, \"I do not think this will ever perish"
  18,36,"and I do not believe that the Hour will ever come. Even if I am returned to my Lord, I shall surely find a better place than this"
  18,37,"His companion replied, in the course of their discussion, \"Do you deny Him who created you from dust, from a small drop of fluid, then formed you into a man"
  18,38,"But as far as I am concerned, God alone is my Lord and I set up no partners with Him"
  18,39,"When you entered your garden, why did you not say, \"That which God wills [will surely come to pass], there is no power save with God?\" Although you see I have less wealth and offspring than you"
  18,40,"my Lord may well give me a garden better than yours and send down thunderbolts from heaven upon your vineyard, turning it into a barren waste"
  18,41,"or its water may sink into the earth, so that you will never be able to find it again"
  18,42,"So it was, and all his fruit was destroyed. The vines had all fallen down on their trellises, and their owner wrung his hands, bewailing all that he had spent on his garden. He said, \"Would that I had not associated anyone with my Lord"
  18,43,"He had no party to help him against God, nor was he able to defend himself"
  18,44,"The only support is from God, the True God. He is the best in rewarding and the best in respect of the final outcome"
  18,45,"Give them an example about worldly life. It is like the vegetation of the earth that thrives when watered by the rain, which We send down from the sky, and then it all becomes stubble which the wind blows away. God has power over all things"